Mr. Townsend says at least 1/2 mi. up - has never followed it far down.

dwc:locality: Found at the Fish Hatchery Branch about 1 1/2 mi. above Hatchery. It is very abundant on both banks for about 1/2 mi. and sometimes solid for 20x12 ft. To be sure to find this go to Fish Hatchery ang go up F.H. Branch (creek) for perhaps 1/2 mile and come to a valley pasture through which the branch runs. A saw mill was located here. There is now a pile of saw dust. Where the branch enters the open pasture from the woods, the Shortia begins and as far up as we went, about 1/4 mi., was in great abundance.
Fuller Tract, upland woods to ravines.
dwc:occurrenceRemarks: Persistent in ravine after transplant from the Carolinas
